# AI Assistant Extension - Environment Configuration

## Extension Environment Variables

The extension is built locally and runs in your browser.
Set this variable BEFORE building to point to your Connector API.

### Local Development
```bash
# Use local connector API (default)
VITE_CONNECTOR_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
```

### Production (Vercel-Hosted Connector API)
```bash
# After deploying connector API to Vercel, use the Vercel URL
VITE_CONNECTOR_API_URL=https://your-project-name.vercel.app
```

## Connector API Environment Variables

Set these in Vercel dashboard after deployment.

### Production (Vercel)
- `NODE_ENV`: production
- `JWT_SECRET`: Strong random key (required! Generate: `openssl rand -base64 32`)
- `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`: `chrome-extension://*,moz-extension://*`

## Deployment Flow

1. **Connector API** → Deploy to Vercel (one-time setup)
2. **Extension** → Build locally with Vercel URL, load into browser
3. **Extension** → Auto-connects to your Vercel API at runtime

## Setup Examples

### Local Development (Both Local)
```bash
# Terminal 1: Connector API
npm run dev:api

# Terminal 2: Extension (uses http://localhost:3001 by default)
npm run dev
```

### Production (API on Vercel, Extension Local)
```bash
# 1. Deploy connector API to Vercel (done once via Vercel dashboard)
# 2. Get your Vercel URL (e.g., https://your-project-name.vercel.app)

# 3. Set environment variable
export VITE_CONNECTOR_API_URL=https://your-project-name.vercel.app

# 4. Build extension (extension.ts and popup scripts will include Vercel URL)
npm run build:chromium
npm run build:firefox

# 5. Load dist/chromium or dist/firefox into browser
# Extension will automatically connect to your Vercel API
```
